==In popular culture==
A fictionalised version of Henry Troyat is featured in the 2014–2015 Image Comics Millarworld comic book series &quot;MPH&quot; by Mark Millar and Duncan Fegredo as the former Chief Scientific Officer of France&#x27;s superhuman development program and inventor of the titular &quot;MPH&quot; super-speed pill, who disappeared in 1984 and has been living in-hiding ever since (bar attending the occasional jazz festival). While Millar revealed in an interview in January 2014 that the character would return in another then-untitled title set in the Millarworld shared fictional universe the following year, which turned out to be &quot;&quot;, the character would be renamed &quot;Orlov&quot; for this follow-up appearance.

